  #Important Minecraft commands: (You can use them in the command line, where you have started your server)
  
  /op name 
  #give the person op. Most comfortable way of using the commands.
  
  /whitelist name
  #If you enable a whitelist you have to give everyone who wants to join the server a permission. Good for Privat servers, that you are hosting in a non-privat network.
  
  /ban name
  #Bans a player. Usefull if you are not ingame at the moment.
  
  #All commands can also be used ingame, if you have a op permission.
